                                                    Staff Information Page

   Merle F. Vigil, Research Soil Scientist
   Acting Research Leader - May, 2000 ...

   Central Great Plains Research Station
   USDA-Agricultural Research Service, Northern Plains Area
   40335 Rd. GG
   Akron, CO 80720
   Phone: 970-345-0517 / 970-345-2259
   FAX: 970-345-2088
   E-Mail: mvigil@lamar.colostate.edu

   Education
          1980 B.S. Agronomy, Colorado State University
          1983 M.S. Soil Fertility, Colorado State University
          1989 Ph.D. Soil Fertility/Soil Chemistry, Kansas State
          University


   Research Interests
          Mineralization-Immobilization of soil organic N and crop residue
          N
          Nitrate leaching through soils
          Crop residue management and nutrient cycling of animal manures
          Fertilizer use efficiency particularly with N fertilizers
          The effect of soil water on N use efficiency
          Management strategies to maximize fertilizer and water use
          efficiencies
          Simulation modeling of the above processes

